    "key2": {
        "title": "UX Design in the IoT Era",
        "abstract": "The current advancement of IoT technology has accelerated the era of hyper-connectivity in our lives. This has vastly driven convergence among different fields along with the expansion of our thoughts and behaviors. However, to provide meaningful experiences, these relational expansions and unprecedented possibilities opened up by IoT need to be founded on core human values. Furthermore, harmonious integration between technology and design is also essential. Today, I would like to talk about what must be done in order to foster the IoT as a human-centered innovation and how UX design can realize the well balanced and harmonious IoT environment.",
        "abstract_j": "IoTの技術の現在の進歩は、私たちの生活の中でハイパーコネクティビティの時代を加速しています。これは非常に私たちの思考や行動の拡大に伴って異なる分野間のコンバージェンスを牽引してきた。しかし、意味のある経験を提供するために、IoTのによって開かこれらの関係の拡張と前例のない可能性がコア人間の価値の上に築かれる必要がある。さらに、技術とデザインの調和の統合も不可欠である。今日、私は人間中心のイノベーションとどのようUXデザインのバランスと調和のとれたIoT環境を実現することができますようにのIoTを育成するためには何をしなければならないかについてお話したいと思います。",
        "abstract_c": "物联网技术目前的发展加速了超级连接时代在我们的生活。这极大地推动趋同随着我们的思想和行为的扩大不同领域之一。然而，提供有意义的经验，这些关系展开了前所未有的可能性开辟物联网需要建立在核心人的价值。此外，技术和设计之间的和谐统一也是必不可少的。今天，我想谈谈什么是必须以促进物联网作为一个以人为本的创新，以及如何UX设计可以实现很好的平衡与和谐的物联网环境下进行。",
        "abstract_k": "만약 IoT 기술의 현재 발전은 우리의 삶에 하이퍼 연결의 시대를 가속화하고있다. 이것은 크게 우리의 생각과 행동의 확대와 함께 다른 분야들 사이에서 통합을 주도하고있다. 그러나, 의미있는 경험, 이러한 관계의 확장과 새로운 가능성의 IoT에 의해 개방 코어 인간의 가치에 설립 할 필요를 제공합니다. 또한, 기술과 디자인 사이의 조화로운 통합은 필수적이다. 오늘은 인간 중심의 혁신과 방법 UX 디자인은 균형과 조화의 IoT 환경을 실현할 수 많은 걸 육성하기 위해 무엇을 할 수 있어야에 대해 이야기하고 싶습니다.",
        "cAndB": "",
        "bio": "Donghoon Chang is Executive VP, Head of Design Strategy Team and UX Center in Corporate Design Center, Samsung Electronics. Since joining Samsung in 2006, he has played a critical role in establishing the company’s design vision for the future which has gradually shifted from a focus on style and convenience to a holistic user experience design and has developed mid to long-term design strategies, including ‘Design 3.0’ which envisions design that delivers new meaning and delight to people and contributes to society by creating sustainable and innovative value.<br/><br/>Chang received two MFA degrees from the School of the Art Institute of Chicago (Chicago, USA) and Seoul National University (Seoul, Korea). He worked for IBM Korea and Time &s; Space Tech inc. as a communications specialist and art director respectively. Before joining Samsung, he was a professor at EWHA Womans University (Seoul, Korea) where he taught visual design, information design as well as user experience design. He was selected as 'the 2nd most creative people in the world' by Fast Company in 2013.",
        "keywords": [],
        "speaker": "Donghoon Chang",
        "speaker-affiliation": "VP, Head of Design Strategy Team and UX Center in Corporate Design Center, Samsung Electronics",
        "type": "keynote",
        "subtype": "keynote",
        "award": false,
        "hm": false
    },
    "key3": {
        "title": "Journey to a Better Life",
        "abstract": "New technologies and devices are coming out every day along with the rapid growth of the internet and enhancement of hardware performance. These trends are connected and tangled with each other. This era of \"Smart\" brings us great benefits and convenience, but there are still many technical hurdles and interface obstacles to be crossed. Now we are able to access massive amount of data, but at the expense of privacy and security. How can we untie this knot? We all strive for the same goal: “to make people’s lives better,” no matter how we define our role in life. In this talk, we will present what we do in LG Electronics to address this goal within the aspects of software engineering and UX design, and also discuss what we should care about when delivering innovative products to the world.",
        "abstract_j": "新しい技術やデバイスがハードウェア性能のインターネットと充実の急速な成長に伴い、毎日出てきている。これらの傾向は、接続されており、相互に絡み合っている。  スマートのこの時代は、私たち大きなメリットと利便性をもたらしますが、多くの技術的なハードルと交差するインターフェイスの障害が残っています。今、私たちは、大量のデータにアクセスすることがありますが、プライバシーとセキュリティを犠牲にして。どのように我々はこの結び目をほどくことができますか？私たちは皆、同じ目標のために努力：「よりよい人々の生活を作るために、「私たちは生活の中で私たちの役割を定義するどんなに。本講演では、我々はソフトウェアエンジニアリングとUXデザインの局面において、この目標に対処するためにLG電子に何をすべきか提示し、また、我々は世界に革新的な製品を提供する際に気にすべきかを説明します。",
        "abstract_c": "新技术和新设备，每天都现身随着互联网的快速增长的硬件性能和增强。这些趋势都连接和相互缠结。对“智能”这个时代给我们带来了极大的实惠和便利，但仍有许多技术障碍和接口的障碍需要跨越。现在我们能够访问数据的巨量，但在隐私和安全性为代价的。我们怎样才能解开这个心结？我们都努力为同一个目标：“使人们的生活更美好，”我们不管如何定义我们在生活中的作用。在这次演讲中，我们将提出我们做什么的LG电子，以解决在软件工程和UX设计方面这一目标，并讨论我们应该关心世界提供创新的产品时。",
        "abstract_k": "새로운 기술과 장치는 하드웨어 성능의 급속한 인터넷의 성장 및 향상과 함께 매일 나오고있다. 이러한 경향 연결하고 서로 얽혀있다.  스마트 이 시대는 우리에게 큰 혜택과 편리함을 제공하지만, 교차 할 많은 기술적 인 장애물 및 인터페이스 장애물은 여전히​​ 존재한다. 이제 우리는 방대한 양의 데이터에 액세스 할 수 있지만 프라이버시와 보안을 희생. 우리는 어떻게이 매듭을 풀어 수 있습니까? 우리는 모두 같은 목표를 위해 노력 더 나은 사람들의 삶을 만들기 위해,우리가 인생에서 우리의 역할을 정의 아무리. 이 이야기에서 우리는 우리가 소프트웨어 엔지니어링 및 UX 디자인의 측면에서이 목표를 해결하기 위해 LG 전자에 무엇을 제시하고, 또한 우리가 세계에 혁신적인 제품을 배달 할 때 걱정해야하는지에 대해 설명합니다.",
        "cAndB": "",
        "bio": "David Min is a Senior Research Fellow at LG Electronics and is head of the Software Center. He is known for spearheading one of the most successful SmartTV platforms in the industry, providing a superior user experience and an open API for 3rd party developers.<br/><br/>David studied computer science and statistics at Seoul National University for BS degree and computer science at Korea Advanced Institute of Science & Technology for MS degree. After four years work at Samsung Co. as an IT system analyst, he went to the USA to enroll in the computer science PhD program at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. After finishing his advanced studies at UIUC, he worked for many years at various companies in computer, software, and consumer electronics industries, including Digital Equipment Corp. (now HP), Microsoft, Samsung Electronics. David joined LG Electronics in 2006.",
        "keywords": [],
        "speaker": "David Min",
        "speaker-affiliation": "Senior Research Fellow, LG Electronics",
        "type": "keynote",
        "subtype": "keynote",
        "award": false,
        "hm": false
    },
    "key4": {
        "title": "ACM-W Athena Lecture: Large-Scale Behavioral Data: Potential and Pitfalls",
        "abstract": "Over the last decade, the rise of web services has made it possible to gather traces of human behavior in situ at a scale and fidelity previously unimaginable. Large-scale behavioral data enables researchers and practitioners to detect adverse drug reactions and interactions, to understand how information diffuses through social networks, how people browse and search for information, how individual learning strategies are related to educational outcome, etc. Using examples from search, I will highlight how observational logs provide a rich new lens onto the diversity of searchers, tasks, and interactivity that characterize information systems today, and how experimental logs have revolutionized the way in which web-based systems are designed and evaluated. Although logs provide a great deal of information about what people are doing, they provide little insight about why they are doing so or whether they are satisfied. Complementary methods from observations, laboratory studies and panels are necessary to provide a more complete understanding of and support for search which is increasingly a core fabric of people’s everyday lives. The CHI community should lead the way in shaping best practices and policy in behavioral log studies.",
        "abstract_j": "過去10年間、ウェブサービスの上昇がスケールでその場で人間の行動の痕跡を収集することを可能にしたと忠実以前には想像もできなかった。大規模行動データは、検索からの例を使用してなど、個々の学習戦略は、教育成果にどのように関連しているか、副作用や相互作用を検出するための情報がソーシャルネットワークを通って拡散するかを理解するために、人々が閲覧方法や情報を検索し、研究者や実務を可能に私は、今日の情報システムを特徴づけるサーチャー、タスク、および双方向性の多様性に豊かな新しいレンズを提供する方法の観測ログ強調表示して、どのように実験的なログのウェブベースのシステムが設計され、評価される方法に革命をもたらしているでしょう。ログは、人々が何をしているかについて多くの情報を提供するが、彼らはそうしている理由について、またはそれらが満たされているかどうか少し洞察力を提供する。観測からの相補の方法は、実験室での研究とパネルはますます人々の日常生活のコア·ファブリックでより完全な理解と検索のためのサポートを提供するために必要である。 CHIコミュニティは、行動ログの研究におけるベストプラクティスと政策の形成に道を導くべきである。",
        "abstract_c": "在过去的十年中，Web服务的兴起，使得有可能聚集在原位人类行为的痕迹，在规模和保真度以前难以想象的。大规模的行为数据使研究人员和从业者，以检测药物的不良反应和相互作用，了解如何扩散的信息通过社交网络，人们如何浏览和搜索信息，如何个性化学习策略与教育成果等使用的搜索样例，我将重点介绍如何观察日志提供了丰富的新镜头上搜索用户，任务和交互今天所特有的信息系统的多样性，以及如何实验日志已经彻底改变了其基于Web的系统的设计和评估的方式。虽然日志提供了大量有关人们正在做什么的信息，他们提供有关他们为什么这样做，或者他们是否满意一点见解。从观测互补的方法，实验室研究和面板是必要的，以提供更完整的理解和对搜索支持这是日益人们日常生活的一个芯部织物。该CHI社会应带头塑造在行为日志研究的最佳实践和政策的方式。",
        "abstract_k": "지난 10 년간, 웹 서비스의 상승이 가능하고 스케일 충실도 이전에 상상 시츄 인간 행동의 흔적을 수집했다. 대규모 행동 데이터는 연구자와 실무자의 정보를 사람이 검색 등 학습 전략은 교육 결과에 관한 방법, 개인 정보, 검색에서 예제를 사용하여 검색하는 방법 소셜 네트워크를 통해 확산 방법을 이해하기 위해, 약물 이상 반응과 상호 작용을 검출 할 수 있습니다 , 오늘은 정보 시스템의 특성을 수색자, 작업 및 상호 작용의 다양성에 풍부한 새로운 렌즈를 제공하는 방법 관찰 로그 강조하는 방법과 실험 로그 웹 기반 시스템 설계 및 평가하는 방식에 혁명을 것입니다. 로그는 사람들이 무엇을하고 있는지에 대한 많은 정보를 제공하지만, 그들은 그렇게 또는 만족 여부를하고있는 이유에 대한 약간의 통찰력을 제공합니다. 관측 보완 방법은 실험실 연구와 패널은 점점 사람들의 일상 생활의 핵심 원단보다 완전한 이해 및 검색에 대한 지원을 제공하는 것이 필요하다. CHI 커뮤니티는 행동 로그 연구의 모범 사례와 정책을 형성하는데 방법을 리드해야합니다.",
        "cAndB": "",
        "bio": "Susan Dumais a Distinguished Scientist at Microsoft and Deputy Managing Director of the Microsoft Research Lab in Redmond. Prior to joining Microsoft Research, she was at Bell Labs and Bellcore, where she worked on Latent Semantic Analysis, techniques for combining search and navigation, and organizational impacts of new technology. Her current research focuses on user modeling and personalization, context and search and temporal dynamics of information. She has worked closely with several Microsoft groups (Bing, Windows Desktop Search, SharePoint, and Office Online Help) on search-related innovations. Susan has published widely in the fields of information science, human-computer interaction and cognitive science, and holds several patents on novel retrieval algorithms and interfaces. Susan is also an adjunct professor in the Information School at the University of Washington. She is Past-Chair of ACM's Special Interest Group in Information Retrieval (SIGIR), and serves on several editorial boards, technical program committees, and government panels. She was elected to the CHI Academy in 2005, an ACM Fellow in 2006, received the SIGIR Gerard Salton Award for Lifetime Achievement 2009, was elected to the National Academy of Engineering (NAE) in 2011, and received the ACM Athena Lecturer Award, and Tony Kent Strix Award in 2014.",
